How to Make Slime without Borax
What you'll need: (Super easy)
1.) 1/4  cup of Glue (clear or white) in a bowl ( use glitter glue or add food coloring if desired)
2.) Add 1 tablespoon of liquid laundry detergent into the same bowl
3.) Stir well, and you may need to add extra liquid laundry detergent if it's too sticky or not slimy enough! 
4.) Have fun and let us know how your slime turn out!

GIANT SLIME IN KIDDLE POOL FUN! In this video Ryan and his family will show you how to make slime (ooze) using household ingredients  that you can do at home! This science experiment is so easy and fun not only for kids, but fun for the whole family! 

What you'll need: (Super easy)
1.) 1 teaspoon of Borax ( can find at any grocery store or Walmart near the laundry detergent) mix with 1 cup of water
2.) Mix a bottle of 4oz glue with 1/2 cup of water in a separate container
3.) Add food coloring to the glue solution
4.) Mix solution with borax and solution with glue together
5.) use your hand and knee the slime 
6.)Drain our the extra water into the sink
7.) Can be store in the fridge to last longer!!!
8.) Have fun and let us know how your slime turn out!

playlist_videos.title: HOW TO MAKE A BOUNCY BALL Easy Science Experiments for kids
playlist_videos.description:
An easy and fun way to make a bouncy ball for kids in 5mins!!! Easy science experiment to do at home!!





HOW TO MAKE A BOUNCY BALL Easy Science Experiments for kids with Thomas and Friends Fun Information
1.) In a cup mix 1 Tb of borax into  1/2 warm water.
2.)In another cup mix  2 Tb  of glue, 1 Tb of  cornstarch, and food coloring of your choice
3.)Pour the glue mixture into the water-borax cup. Leave it in there for about 10 seconds o harden 
4.) Use a spoon or a fork take out the harden mixture squish it with your hands. If it is still sticky, put in back into the water for a few seconds. 
5.) Roll the mixture in your hands to make a ball. The more you roll it, the firmer it will get!
6.) Enjoy your new Bouncy Ball!!!
